{"word":"ἧσσα","slug":"ἧσσα","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἧσσα</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἥσσων'><el>ἥσσων</el></a>\n<p/><i>a defeat, discomfiture</i>, <a href='S:opposed to'>opp. to</a> <el>νίκη</el>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>:—<a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a> rei, <i>a giving way to</i> a thing, <el>ἡδονῶν, ἐπιθυμιῶν</el> <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/>"}]}